"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the overall distribution of product categories in terms of total sales volumes. Next, the user selects a category of interest in View 1, which filters the revenue contributions displayed in View 2 via a [pie chart at the Exploration level]. Then, the relationships between unit price and sales volume for individual products within the selected category are analyzed in View 3 at the [Exploration] level via a scatter plot. The user then examines temporal sales and revenue trends in View 4, also at the [Exploration] level, using an interactive line chart. Finally, a heatmap in View 5 at the [Insight] level highlights category performance trends across months, enabling the identification of patterns for decision-making considerations."